-- Billionaire Batista Buys Stake in Canada’s Miner Ivanplats
-- B y   L u c i a   K a s s a i
-- 2012-10-20T18:32:50Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-20/billionaire-batista-buys-stake-in-canada-s-miner-ivanplats.html
Brazilian billionaire  Eike Batista ’s
EBX Group Co. agreed to buy a 4 percent stake in Canadian mining
company Ivanplats Ltd., according to an e-mailed statement from
EBX today.  Ivanplats, based in Vancouver, raised C$300.8 million
($302.7 million) in an initial public offering on Oct. 16.
Proceeds will be used to develop mines in Africa, the company
said. Ivanplats was founded by billionaire American investor
Robert Friedland.  The acquisition was reported today by Sao Paulo-based
magazine Veja.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Lucia Kassai in  Sao Paulo  at 
